Uses of Package
com.jinvoke

Packages that use com.jinvoke
com.jinvoke Provides annotations and classes for calling native functions from Java. 
com.jinvoke.win32 Provides helper classes that contain J/Invoke declaration of functions for common Win32 DLLs. 
com.jinvoke.win32.structs Provides helper classes that represent the most commonly used Win32 structs. 
 

Classes in com.jinvoke used by com.jinvoke
CallingConvention
          Indicates the calling convention of a native function.
Charset
          Indicates how Java Strings are converted when passing to native code.
 

Classes in com.jinvoke used by com.jinvoke.win32
Callback
          Exposes a Java method as a callback function that can be called by native code.
NativeImport
          Indicates that the annotated method is imported from a native dynamic-link library(dll) or shared library(.so).
 

Classes in com.jinvoke used by com.jinvoke.win32.structs
Callback
          Exposes a Java method as a callback function that can be called by native code.
Embedded
          The @Embedded annotation is used to declare fixed-size Strings and arrays embedded in structures.
NativeStruct
          Indicates that the annotated Java class represents a native structure (struct).
